                    <h1>PAYMENT </h1>
                    <h6>LIFECYCLE OF TRANSACTIONS &lt; $2500.00</h6>
                    <p>For transactions $2500.00 or less, buyers make their purchase → Seller is notified→Buyer populates his shipping address → Seller populates shipping cost → HBA System generates invoice → Buyer makes purchase with ACH through Buyer dashboard → Seller provides tracking number to buyer via dashboard → Ships product → Seller is paid → Success, transaction complete.</p>
                    <h6>LIFECYCLE OF TRANSACTIONS &gt; $2501.00 - $15,000.00</h6>
                    <p>Buyer selects item to purchase → Buyer &amp; Seller agree to transaction initial terms → Transaction Coordinator makes introduction via recorded conference call → SOPs, Samples, quarantine, purchase contract, logistics/insurance are discussed and agreed upon → Purchase contract is completed by both parties → purchase contract is uploaded into system → Buyer sends funds to HBA → Product is transported per terms of the agreement/contract executed → Buyer receives the product → HBA pays the seller
                    </p>
                    <h6>LIFECYCLE OF TRANSACTIONS &gt; $15,001.00</h6>
                    <p>Buyer selects item to purchase → Buyer &amp; Seller agree to transaction initial terms → Transaction Coordinator makes introduction via recorded conference call→ SOPs, Samples, quarantine, purchase contract, logistics/insurance are discussed and agreed upon → Purchase contract is executed by both parties → purchase contract is uploaded into system → Seller chooses escrow/attorney service → Transaction Coordinator sends transaction details to designated escrow/attorneys → Escrow is opened → Buyer deposit funds into escrow → Escrow/Attorney verifies the funds → Product is transported per terms of the agreement → Buyer receives the product → Escrow pays the seller</p>

                </div>
