                <div class="media-body">
                    <h1>Glossary of Terms</h1>
                    <p><b>Start price - </b>The likely starting bid for a given auction, set by the seller at the time of listing.
                    </p>
                    <p><b>Authorized Representative - </b>Someone who you choose to act on your behalf within the HBA Auction/Market. The authorized representative has the legal authority to act on your behalf. <a>Download a Authorized Business Representative Form Here</a>
                    </p>
                    <b>Examples: </b>
                    <p><b>1 ) </b> Registered member/broker using an authorized representative agreement to sell materials on behalf of other registered members.</p>
                    <p><b>2 ) </b>Cooperative representative who has the legal authority to represent and transact business on behalf of the registered cooperative members behalf.</p>
                    <p><b>3 ) </b>Principle, employee or representative of a company authorized to transact business on behalf of a registered company member. </p>
                </div>
                <div class="media-body">
                    <h1>Escrow - How it works </h1>
                    <p>Escrow is a financial instrument held by an independent third party on behalf of the two other parties who are completing a transaction. It’s like a trust account held by a third party while all the seller and buyer’s obligations are fulfilled. All the details of the contract are completed and fulfilled, then funds are released to the seller.
                    </p>
